block title
  title "References"

block content
  main(class="tpage")
    include components/large-nav
    article
      h1 Resources, Reading, and References

      h2 My Favorite Nix Tutorials

      :markdown-it
        NixOS changes very quickly quickly. 
        Whether you feel the changes are because Nix is an immature product, or because Nix has a 
        passionate community, it can be hard to find the documentation you need. These are some
        of the resources I always go go back to.

      h2 Site References

      :markdown-it
        The following software tools and documentation pages are references in the tutorial.
        Archive.org links are included to prevent link rot.

      h3 Tools

      table
        thead 
          tr
            td
              strong Site
            td
              strong Description
            td
              strong Archive Link
        tbody
          tr(id="ref-determinate-installer")
            td
              a(href="https://github.com/DeterminateSystems/nix-installer") Determinate Systems' Nix Installer
            td
              p The <code> nix-installer </code> tool by Determinate Systems is the easiest way to bring Nix to your current system without installing NixOS.
            td
              a(href="https://web.archive.org/web/20231102111419/https://github.com/DeterminateSystems/nix-installer") November 2, 2023
          tr(id="ref-nix-wsl")
            td
              a(href="https://github.com/nix-community/NixOS-WSL") NixOS on WSL
            td
              p This project provides a distribution image of NixOS that you can run on Windows WSL.
            td
              a(href="https://web.archive.org/web/20231126104625/https://github.com/nix-community/NixOS-WSL") November 26, 2023
          tr(id="ref-nixops")
            td
              a(href="https://releases.nixos.org/nixops/latest/manual/manual.html") NixOps Documentation
            td
              p NixOps allows you to deploy NixOS onto cloud-based virtual machines, like Amazon EC2 or a Digital Ocean Droplet.
            td
              a(href="https://web.archive.org/web/20230516102930/https://releases.nixos.org/nixops/latest/manual/manual.html") May 16, 2023
          tr(id="ref-nil")
            td
              a(href="https://github.com/oxalica/nil") Nil
            td
              p Probably Nix's best Language Server. Can be used with many different editors and IDEs.
            td
              a(href="https://web.archive.org/web/20231115151844/https://github.com/oxalica/nil") November 15, 2023
          tr(id="ref-alejandra")
            td
              a(href="https://github.com/kamadorueda/alejandra") Alejandra
            td
              p A handy Nix formatting tool.
            td
              a(href="https://web.archive.org/web/20231125123606/https://github.com/kamadorueda/alejandra") November 25, 2023
          tr(id="ref-vscode")
            td
              a(href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=jnoortheen.nix-ide") Nix IDE for VSCode
            td
              p A general purpose Nix extension for VSCode that can use Nil and Alejandra
            td
              a(href="https://web.archive.org/web/20230321212929/https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=jnoortheen.nix-ide") March 21, 2023
          tr(id="ref-vim")
            td
              a(href="https://github.com/nix-community/nixvim") Nixvim
            td
              p An entire Neovim distribution build for and with Nix.
            td
              a(href="https://web.archive.org/web/20231115082959/https://github.com/nix-community/nixvim") November 15, 2023
          tr(id="ref-flakehub")
            td
              a(href="https://flakehub.com/flakes") Flakehub
            td
              p Flakehub is a repository for Nix flakes. This means that it is a package manager of package builders.
            td
              p NA

